Created 1894 from the part of the parish of Feckenham in Redditch 
    Urban District. See also Table 2, note (a).

In 1889 the part of the parish of Ipsley in Redditch Urban 
    District became part of Worcestershire, in 1894 this area became the 
    separate parish of Upper Ipsley and thereafter Ipsley was again wholly in 
    Warwickshire, until it was transferred of Worcestershire on 1.4.1931. See also Table 2, notes (a) and 
    (f).

Transferred from Worcestershire to Warwickshire on 30.9.1896. 
    See also Table 2, note (f).
Abolished 1.4.1949 and added to the parish of Ipsley.

Created 1894 from the part of the parish of Ipsley in Redditch 
    Urban District. See also Table 2, note (a).
